<subSubSection id="C6878F80462BFFE0FF4FFAE3FE37F981" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8E22DC0B462BFFE0FF4FFAE3FBEBFA52" blockId="6.[136,1452,1290,1633]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="BCE90019462BFFE0FF4FFAE3FF67FAC5" bold="true" box="[136,201,1291,1317]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Notes</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="BCE90019462BFFE0FF16FAE3FF44FAC4" box="[209,234,1291,1316]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">—</emphasis>
When describing 
<taxonomicName id="499DA788462BFFE0FE6AFAE2FD2CFAC4" box="[429,642,1290,1316]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="organensis">
<emphasis id="BCE90019462BFFE0FE6AFAE2FD2CFAC4" box="[429,642,1290,1316]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Lobelia organensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EA0CA1FA462BFFE0FD48FAE2FC95FAC5" author="Gardner, G." box="[655,827,1290,1317]" firstAuthor="Gardner" journalOrPublisher="London Journal of Botany" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" pagination="97 - 137" part="4" refId="ref6971" refString="Gardner, G. (1845) Contributions towards flora of Brazil. London Journal of Botany 4: 97 - 137." title="Contributions towards flora of Brazil" type="journal article" year="1845">Gardner (1845)</bibRefCitation>
referred to the specimen 
<emphasis id="BCE90019462BFFE0FB94FAE2FB5EFAC4" box="[1107,1264,1290,1316]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Gardner 5798</emphasis>
, collected in 
<collectingRegion id="4C5912E9462BFFE0FA44FAE2FF52FAA7" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
and with two duplicates housed at K. We designate the specimen K000494312, with a label in Gardner’s hand and a description of habitat that more closely matches the protologue, as the 
<typeStatus id="512662A9462BFFE0FBCFFAB9FBDCFA8B" box="[1032,1138,1361,1387]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">lectotype</typeStatus>
.A photograph of a duplicate of 
<emphasis id="BCE90019462BFFE0FF61FA9CFEEBFA6E" box="[166,325,1396,1422]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Gardner 5798</emphasis>
that once belonged to W is available in the Field Museum photo negatives collection. That duplicate was not found in the online collection and was probably lost during the World War II.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8E22DC0B462BFFE0FF7AFA52FE37F981" blockId="6.[136,1452,1290,1633]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
Analyzing the 
<typeStatus id="512662A9462BFFE0FEA4FA53FE3DFA35" box="[355,403,1467,1493]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="499DA788462BFFE0FE7DFA52FD27FA34" authorityName="Wimmer" authorityYear="1935" box="[442,649,1466,1492]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="imperialis">
<emphasis id="BCE90019462BFFE0FE7DFA52FD27FA34" box="[442,649,1466,1492]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Lobelia imperialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
we opted to include it as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="499DA788462BFFE0FB89FA53FB48FA34" authorityName=", Gardner" authorityYear="1845" box="[1102,1254,1467,1492]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="organensis">
<emphasis id="BCE90019462BFFE0FB89FA53FB48FA34" box="[1102,1254,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">L. organensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, since there were no reliable traits supporting the recognition of this species as distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="499DA788462BFFE0FC04FA36FBF4FA17" authorityName=", Gardner" authorityYear="1845" box="[963,1114,1502,1527]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="organensis">
<emphasis id="BCE90019462BFFE0FC04FA36FBF4FA17" box="[963,1114,1502,1527]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">L. organensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both taxa exhibit glabrescent leaves, small deflexed bracts, and the ovary about 3/4 free from the hypanthium. The synonymization also applies to the name 
<taxonomicName id="499DA788462BFFE0FEDEF9CDFD96F9DE" authorityName="Wimmer" authorityYear="1953" box="[281,568,1572,1598]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="imperialis" variety="kanitzii">
<emphasis id="BCE90019462BFFE0FEDEF9CDFE87F9DE" box="[281,297,1573,1598]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BCE90019462BFFE0FEFEF9CCFE05F9DE" box="[313,427,1572,1598]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">imperialis</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="BCE90019462BFFE0FE21F9CCFD96F9DE" box="[486,568,1572,1598]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">kanitzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with its 
<typeStatus id="512662A9462BFFE0FD6FF9CCFD76F9DE" box="[680,728,1572,1598]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">type</typeStatus>
being quite similar to 
<taxonomicName id="499DA788462BFFE0FC26F9CDFBD5F9DE" authorityName=", Gardner" authorityYear="1845" box="[993,1147,1572,1598]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="organensis">
<emphasis id="BCE90019462BFFE0FC26F9CDFC5FF9DE" box="[993,1009,1573,1598]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BCE90019462BFFE0FBC6F9CDFBD5F9DE" box="[1025,1147,1573,1598]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">organensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and presenting only small inconsistent differences.
</paragraph>
